{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d736511-bf63-44fa-a509-8cd33a81b497","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening:\n\n## 1. Tests lost history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the default **test ID strategy**. The fully-qualified name now includes the namespace, which changes the stable ID Azure DevOps uses to track test history. To restore continuity, add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<TestIdGenerationStrategy>DisplayName</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n```\n\n…or keep the legacy behavior with the `FullyQualifiedName` option matching v3's format.\n\n## 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a **class-level context** — it no longer carries individual test info. Accessing `TestName` throws `InvalidOperationException`. This is by design; class init runs once and isn't associated with a specific test.\n\n**Fix:** Remove the `TestName` access from `ClassInit`, or move that logic to `[TestInitialize]` where `TestContext` is per-test.\n\n## 3. Other v4 breaking changes to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| **Parallelism** | Tests run in parallel by default. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` or disable if you have shared state. |\n| **Timeout** | `[Timeout]` now defaults to **milliseconds** (not seconds). Verify existing values. |\n| **Assert.ThrowsException** | Now also catches derived exception types (was exact-match in v3). |\n| **DataRow display** | `[DataRow]` test case display names changed format, which can also affect ADO history. |\n| **ClassCleanup** | Default timing changed to run at end of class (was end of assembly). |\n\nWould you like me to update your project file or test code with fixes for issues #1 and #2?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"994e0f4e-59cc-45d6-a249-d4968465cf1b","outputTokens":468,"requestId":"BD00:2CA3BD:20472CE:248869A:6A07D5CC"},"id":"622d53a7-985d-428e-87db-9b7ca2bdd801","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:26:32.810Z","parentId":"65c6f15d-1c93-43ca-8cf5-f154f3a5b678"}
